{"name":"Staggering","type":"weaponFusion","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/classes/desperate_defense.png","data":{"price":400,"description":"<p>A staggering weapon gains the stagger critical hit effect (page 57). If the weapon already has the stagger critical hit effect, the target is staggered for 2 rounds on a critical hit, rather than just 1 round.</p>","isTech":true,"isMagic":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{},"_id":"2lF32qzfzsE5m0mM"}
{"name":"Illuminating","type":"weaponFusion","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/classes/getem.png","data":{"price":400,"description":"<p>Any target you damage with an illuminating weapon glows brightly until the end of your next turn, negating any darkness within 30 feet of it.</p>","isTech":true,"isMagic":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{},"_id":"3OeNPWZTZoQxlhyf"}
{"name":"Disruptive","type":"weaponFusion","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/classes/againts_the_odds.png","data":{"price":400,"description":"<p>A disruptive weapon is especially harmful to undead creatures (those with the undead immunities defensive ability, such as bone troopers and cybernetic zombies). Attacks from a disruptive weapon deal 1d4 extra damage to undead creatures.</p>","isTech":true,"isMagic":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{},"_id":"9XJv85HtvmGrW4DE"}
{"name":"Accurate","type":"weaponFusion","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/classes/laser_accuracy.png","data":{"price":400,"description":"<p>An accurate weapon can be aimed more carefully&nbsp; to make particularly accurate attacks with it. If you give up your move before taking an attack action with an accurate weapon, you gain a +1 bonus to your attack roll.</p>","isTech":true,"isMagic":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{},"_id":"BPM6tDcVCytsD1iV"}
{"name":"Defending","type":"weaponFusion","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/classes/blue_20.png","data":{"price":400,"description":"<p>When you take the Defend action (page 82) while holding a defending weapon, you gain an additional +2 bonus to your Armor Class.</p>","isTech":true,"isMagic":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{},"_id":"G743f4UHG9fiG6gC"}
{"name":"Inspiring","type":"weaponFusion","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/classes/starlight_form.png","data":{"price":400,"description":"<p>Attacks from an inspiring weapon can fill you and your allies with confidence. When you score a critical hit (page 78) with an inspiring weapon, you and allies within 60 feet gain a +2 bonus to saving throws for 1&nbsp;minute.</p>","isTech":true,"isMagic":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{},"_id":"LjLnbIoacu6wUpWq"}
{"name":"Knockdown","type":"weaponFusion","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/classes/blazing_orbit.png","data":{"price":400,"description":"<p>You can add the knockdown fusion only to weapons that deal kinetic damage. A knockdown weapon gains the knockdown critical hit effect (page 57). If the weapon already has that effect, the target loses its move for 2 rounds on a critical hit, rather than just 1 round.</p>","isTech":true,"isMagic":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{},"_id":"TW6zrNnpSpnheX1B"}
{"name":"Blasting","type":"weaponFusion","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/classes/opening_volley.png","data":{"price":400,"description":"<p>You can add the blasting fusion only to a small arm or longarm. Once per day, you can use a blasting weapon to make one attack using the blast weapon special property (page 56), treating its range as 15 feet.</p>","isTech":true,"isMagic":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{},"_id":"WmqVXOrBByPLHzZW"}
